One thing that often holds people back from writing articles or
posts on sites like Linkedin is not knowing where to start.

So, I wanted to provide four key types of content you can write
for LinkedIn posts, as well as links to examples!

Sharing Your Expertise Posts

One great style of posts is one that shows off your expertise. If
you're the Snowflake or Databricks person, show it. Create
diagrams or posts that show your expertise in these tools. That
way, if you have viewers in your audience who have questions on
the topic, you become the person to answer them. Two individuals
