A classic approach to any form of copy is to clearly state a
problem and then a solution. This also works for LinkedIn. There
are plenty of problems your clients probably face. For example,
picking the right technical solution out of dozens of solutions,
hiring, and, of course, the problem with schema changes. I
believe that one person who does this well is =E2=80=8BChad Sanderson=E2=80=
